2[i].length`\n\n- `1 <= n <= 30`\n\n- `img1[i][j]` is either `0` or `1`.\n\n- `img2[i][j]` is either `0` or `1`.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/image-overlap/","problemName":"Image Overlap","problemNumber":835,"problemSlug":"image-overlap","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":835,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Math","Geometry"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"An axis-aligned rectangle is represented as a list `[x1, y1, x2, y2]`, where `(x1, y1)` is the coordinate of its bottom-left corner, and `(x2, y2)` is the coordinate of its top-right corner. Its top and bottom edges are parallel to the X-axis, and its left and right edges are parallel to the Y-axis.\n\nTwo rectangles overlap if the area of their intersection is **positive**. To be clear, two rectangles that only touch at the corner or edges do not overlap.\n\nGiven two axis-aligned rectangles `rec1` and `rec2`, return `true`* if they overlap, otherwise return *`false`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: rec1 = [0,0,2,2], rec2 = [1,1,3,3]\nOutput: true","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: rec1 = [0,0,1,1], rec2 = [1,0,2,1]\nOutput: false","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: rec1 = [0,0,1,1], rec2 = [2,2,3,3]\nOutput: false","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `rec1.length == 4`\n\n- `rec2.length == 4`\n\n- `-10⁹ <= rec1[i], rec2[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `rec1` and `rec2` represent a valid rectangle with a non-zero area.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Math","Geometry"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"An axis-aligned rectangle is represented as a list `[x1, y1, x2, y2]`, where `(x1, y1)` is the coordinate of its bottom-left corner, and `(x2, y2)` is the coordinate of its top-right corner. Its top and bottom edges are parallel to the X-axis, and its left and right edges are parallel to the Y-axis.\n\nTwo rectangles overlap if the area of their intersection is **positive**. To be clear, two rectangles that only touch at the corner or edges do not overlap.\n\nGiven two axis-aligned rectangles `rec1` and `rec2`, return `true`* if they overlap, otherwise return *`false`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: rec1 = [0,0,2,2], rec2 = [1,1,3,3]\nOutput: true\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: rec1 = [0,0,1,1], rec2 = [1,0,2,1]\nOutput: false\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: rec1 = [0,0,1,1], rec2 = [2,2,3,3]\nOutput: false\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `rec1.length == 4`\n\n- `rec2.length == 4`\n\n- `-10⁹ <= rec1[i], rec2[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `rec1` and `rec2` represent a valid rectangle with a non-zero area.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/rectangle-overlap/","problemName":"Rectangle Overlap","problemNumber":836,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"An axis-aligned rectangle is represented as a list `[x1, y1, x2, y2]`, where `(x1, y1)` is the coordinate of its bottom-left corner, and `(x2, y2)` is the coordinate of its top-right corner. Its top and bottom edges are parallel to the X-axis, and its left and right edges are parallel to the Y-axis.\n\nTwo rectangles overlap if the area of their intersection is **positive**. To be clear, two rectangles that only touch at the corner or edges do not overlap.\n\nGiven two axis-aligned rectangles `rec1` and `rec2`, return `true`* if they overlap, otherwise return *`false`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: rec1 = [0,0,2,2], rec2 = [1,1,3,3]\nOutput: true","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: rec1 = [0,0,1,1], rec2 = [1,0,2,1]\nOutput: false","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"se