 `maxPts` is an integer. Each draw is independent and the outcomes have equal probabilities.\n\nAlice stops drawing numbers when she gets `k` **or more points**.\n\nReturn the probability that Alice has `n` or fewer points.\n\nAnswers within `10⁻⁵` of the actual answer are considered accepted.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: n = 10, k = 1, maxPts = 10\nOutput: 1.00000\nExplanation: Alice gets a single card, then stops.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: n = 6, k = 1, maxPts = 10\nOutput: 0.60000\nExplanation: Alice gets a single card, then stops.\nIn 6 out of 10 possibilities, she is at or below 6 points.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: n = 21, k = 17, maxPts = 10\nOutput: 0.73278","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `0 <= k <= n <= 10⁴`\n\n- `1 <= maxPts <= 10⁴`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Math","Dynamic Programming","Sliding Window","Probability and Statistics"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Alice plays the following game, loosely based on the card game **\"21\"**.\n\nAlice starts with `0` points and draws numbers while she has less than `k` points. During each draw, she gains an integer number of points randomly from the range `[1, maxPts]`, where `maxPts` is an integer. Each draw is independent and the outcomes have equal probabilities.\n\nAlice stops drawing numbers when she gets `k` **or more points**.\n\nReturn the probability that Alice has `n` or fewer points.\n\nAnswers within `10⁻⁵` of the actual answer are considered accepted.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: n = 10, k = 1, maxPts = 10\nOutput: 1.00000\nExplanation: Alice gets a single card, then stops.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: n = 6, k = 1, maxPts = 10\nOutput: 0.60000\nExplanation: Alice gets a single card, then stops.\nIn 6 out o