ocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a string `s` of lowercase English letters and an integer array `shifts` of the same length.\n\nCall the `shift()` of a letter, the next letter in the alphabet, (wrapping around so that `'z'` becomes `'a'`).\n\n- For example, `shift('a') = 'b'`, `shift('t') = 'u'`, and `shift('z') = 'a'`.\n\nNow for each `shifts[i] = x`, we want to shift the first `i + 1` letters of `s`, `x` times.\n\nReturn *the final string after all such shifts to s are applied*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: s = \"abc\", shifts = [3,5,9]\nOutput: \"rpl\"\nExplanation: We start with \"abc\".\nAfter shifting the first 1 letters of s by 3, we have \"dbc\".\nAfter shifting the first 2 letters of s by 5, we have \"igc\".\nAfter shifting the first 3 letters of s by 9, we have \"rpl\", the answer.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: s = \"aaa\", shifts = [1,2,3]\nOutput: \"gfd\"","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= s.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `s` consists of lowercase English letters.\n\n- `shifts.length == s.length`\n\n- `0 <= shifts[i] <= 10⁹`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","String","Prefix Sum"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a string `s` of lowercase English letters and an integer array `shifts` of the same length.\n\nCall the `shift()` of a letter, the next letter in the alphabet, (wrapping around so that `'z'` becomes `'a'`).\n\n- For example, `shift('a') = 'b'`, `shift('t') = 'u'`, and `shift('z') = 'a'`.\n\nNow for each `shifts[i] = x`, we want to shift the first `i + 1` letters of `s`, `x` times.\n\nReturn *the final string after all such shifts to s are applied*.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: s = \"abc\", shifts = [3,5,9]\nOutput: \"rpl\"\nExplanation: We start with \"abc\".\nAfter shifting the first 1 lette