leetcode.com/problems/stone-game/","problemName":"Stone Game","problemNumber":877,"problemSlug":"stone-game","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":877,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Math","Binary Search"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"A positive integer is *magical* if it is divisible by either `a` or `b`.\n\nGiven the three integers `n`, `a`, and `b`, return the `n^(th)` magical number. Since the answer may be very large, **return it modulo **`10⁹ + 7`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: n = 1, a = 2, b = 3\nOutput: 2","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: n = 4, a = 2, b = 3\nOutput: 6","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n <= 10⁹`\n\n- `2 <= a, b <= 4 * 10⁴`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Math","Binary Search"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Hard","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"A positive integer is *magical* if it is divisible by either `a` or `b`.\n\nGiven the three integers `n`, `a`, and `b`, return the `n^(th)` magical number. Since the answer may be very large, **return it modulo **`10⁹ + 7`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: n = 1, a = 2, b = 3\nOutput: 2\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: n = 4, a = 2, b = 3\nOutput: 6\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n <= 10⁹`\n\n- `2 <= a, b <= 4 * 10⁴`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/nth-magical-number/","problemName":"Nth Magical Number","problemNumber":878,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"A positive integer is *magical* if it is divisible by either `a` or `b`.\n\nGiven the three integers `n`, `a`, and `b`, return the `n^(th)` magical number. Since the answer may be very large, **return it modulo **`10⁹ + 7`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence"